 Social Sciences (1998). Since that time, in hundreds of empirical studies, these methods have been tested and integrated with qualitative, quantitative, and mixed-method research designs. Anderson and Braud, writing with a contribution from Jennifer Clements, invite scholars to bring multiple ways of knowing and personal resources to their scholarship. While emphasizing established research conventions for rigor, Anderson and Braud encourage researchers to plumb the depths of intuition, imagination, play, mindfulness, compassion, creativity, and embodied writing as research skills. Experiential exercises to help readers develop these skills are provided.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aPsychologyxResearchxMethodology. 0aSocial sciencesxResearchxMethodology. 0aTranspersonal psychologyxResearchxMethodology. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Educational Psychology. 4aHealth and Medicine : Health and Society. 4aPsychology : Psychology. 4aPsychology : Transpersonal Psychology. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Movements / Transpersonal.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Rosemarie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraud, William, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBraud, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClements, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438436739423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438436739/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles